gent-integration-checklist.md` — Design principles and validation criteria\\n\\n## Command Routing\\n\\nWhen the user invokes this skill:\\n\\n1. **Parse the argument** after `/agent-integration` to determine which command to run\\n2. **If no argument**, ask which command they want: `research`, `write-tests`, or `implement`\\n3. **If parameters aren't set yet**, collect them before proceeding\\n4. **Load the corresponding prompt file** and follow its instructions\\n\\n### Typical workflow order\\n\\n```\\n/agent-integration research      # Phase 1: Assess compatibility\\n/agent-integration write-tests   # Phase 2: Write test suite\\n/agent-integration implement     # Phase 3: Build via TDD\\n```\\n\\nEach phase can be run independently, but later phases work best with earlier phase outputs available.\\n\",\"numLines\":70,\"startLine\":1,\"totalLines\":70}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"34a256e2-fd39-4d99-88af-69ed6161b4b7\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"647a7d3a-c5e0-4d29-ae1c-59909091f417\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"e9db4320-d865-4145-8cc5-ce4f391630bc\",\"version\":\"2.1.58\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/agent-integration-skill\",\"slug\":\"sparkling-gathering-hejlsberg\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01RWM4yD1MvkCaUknYiqwCt7\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"Now I understand the picture. Let me look at how the `commit-commands` plugin works with its `:` subcommand pattern, since that's what the user wants to emulate.\\n\\nLooking at the file listing:\\n- `commit-commands:commit` and `commit-commands:commit-push-pr` and `commit-commands:clean_gone` - these appear in the skill list from the system prompt\\n- `claude-md-management:revise-claude-md` and `claude-md-management:claude-md-improver` - these also appear\\n- `ralph-loop:help`, `ralph-loop:cancel-ralph`, `ralph-loop:ralph-loop` - these too\\n\\n\\nThese 