e2e/tests/main_test.go` — `TestMain` builds the CLI binary (via `entire.BinPath()`), runs preflight checks for required binaries (git, tmux, agent CLIs), sets up artifact directories, and configures env\\n    17→2. `e2e/testutil/repo.go` — `RepoState` struct (holds agent, dir, artifact dir, head/checkpoint refs), `SetupRepo` (creates temp git repo, runs `entire enable`, patches settings), `ForEachAgent` (runs a test per registered agent with repo setup, concurrency gating, and timeout scaling)\\n    18→3. `e2e/agents/agent.go` — `Agent` interface (`Name`, `Binary`, `EntireAgent`, `PromptPattern`, `TimeoutMultiplier`, `RunPrompt`, `StartSession`, `Bootstrap`, `IsTransientError`), `Register()` for agent self-registration in `init()`, `RegisterGate()` for concurrency limits, `AcquireSlot`/`ReleaseSlot` for gating\\n    19→4. `e2e/agents/tmux.go` — `TmuxSession` for interactive PTY-based tests: `NewTmuxSession`, `Send`, `SendKeys`, `WaitFor` (with settle-time logic), `Capture`, `Close`\\n    20→5. `e2e/testutil/assertions.go` — Rich assertion helpers: `AssertFileExists`, `WaitForFileExists`, `AssertNewCommits`, `WaitForCheckpoint`, `AssertCheckpointAdvanced`, `AssertHasCheckpointTrailer`, `AssertCheckpointExists`, `AssertCommitLinkedToCheckpoint`, `AssertCheckpointMetadataComplete`, `ValidateCheckpointDeep`, and many more\\n    21→6. `e2e/testutil/metadata.go` — `CheckpointMetadata`, `SessionMetadata`, `TokenUsage`, `Attribution`, `SessionRef` types; `CheckpointPath()` helper for sharded directory layout\\n    22→7. `e2e/entire/entire.go` — CLI wrapper: `BinPath()` (builds from source or uses `E2E_ENTIRE_BIN`), `Enable`, `Disable`, `RewindList`, `Rewind`, `RewindLogsOnly`, `Explain`, `ExplainGenerate`, `ExplainCommit`, `Resume`\\n    23→8. `e2e/testutil/artifacts.go` — Automatic artifact capture via `t.Cleanup`: `CaptureArtifacts` saves git-log, git-tree, checkpoint metadata, entire logs, and tmux pane content\\n    24→\\n    25→### Step 2: Read Existing E2E Test Scenarios\\n    26→\\n    27→Run `Glob(\\\"e2e/tests/*_test.go\\\")` to find all existing test files. Read a few to understand the patterns:\\n    28→- How tests use `testutil.ForEachAgent` with a timeout and callback `func(t, s, ctx)`\\n    29→- How prompts are written inline (no separate prompt template file)\\n    30→- How `s.RunPrompt`, `s.Git`, `s.StartSession`, `s.WaitFor`, `s.Send` are used\\n    31→- How assertions validate checkpoints, rewind, metadata, etc.\\n    32→\\n    33→### Step 3: Read Checkpoint Scenarios Doc\\n    34→\\n    35→Read `docs/architecture/checkpoint-scenarios.md` for the state machine and scenarios the tests should cover.\\n    36→\\n    37→### Step 4: Create Agent Implementation\\n    38→\\n    39→Add a new `Agent` implementation in `e2e/agents/${agent_slug}.go`:\\n    40→\\n    41→**Pattern to follow** (based on existing implementations like `claude.go`, `gemini.go`, `opencode.go`):\\n    42→\\n    43→```go\\n    44→package agents\\n    45→\\n    46→import (\\n    47→\\t\\\"context\\\"\\n    48→\\t\\\"errors\\\"\\n    49→\\t\\\"fmt\\\"\\n    50→\\t\\\"os\\\"\\n    51→\\t\\\"os/exec\\\"\\n    52→\\t\\\"strings\\\"\\n    53→\\t\\\"syscall\\\"\\n    54→\\t\\\"time\\\"\\n    55→)\\n    56→\\n    57→func init() {\\n    58→\\tif env := os.Getenv(\\\"E2E_AGENT\\\"); env != \\\"\\\" && env != \\\"${agent-slug}\\\" {\\n    59→\\t\\treturn\\n    60→\\t}\\n    61→\\tRegister(&${AgentName}{})\\n    62→\\t// Optional: limit concurrency for rate-limited agents\\n    63→\\t// RegisterGate(\\\"${agent-slug}\\\", 1)\\n    64→}\\n    65→\\n    66→type ${AgentName} struct{}\\n    67→\\n    68→func (a *${AgentName}) Name() string               { return \\\"${agent-slug}\\\" }\\n    69→func (a *${AgentName}) Binary() string             { return \\\"${binary-name}\\\" }\\n    70→func (a *${AgentName}) EntireAgent() string        { return \\\"${entire-agent-name}\\\" }\\n    71→func (a *${AgentName}) PromptPattern() string      { return `${prompt-regex}` }\\n   